I Summon Pot of Greed! 🃏 

My inspiration for this pot comes from Yu-Gi-Oh, a trading card game that I used to play when I was little. 

Crafted with 10 pounds of clay, this pot marks my first venture into creating a pottery masterpiece with a face.

Comment below and share your ideas for the next pot I should bring to life! 🌱🏺

#art #pottery #oddlysatisfying #yugioh #fyp

Love’s strength conquers all obstacles 💕

Happy Fail Friday! Here’s a throwback to my first-ever recorded throwing session back in 2018, when I was under the apprenticeship of the amazing @dannymeisinger 

During this session, I attempted to create 1-pound mugs inspired by Danny’s techniques. While I didn’t manage to finish a single piece that day, I held my head high and continued pushing forward.

#art #pottery #glazed #oddlysatisfying #fyp

A delightful private class with Darren from @lovehandleclay ! ✨ 

We focused on spiral wedging, throwing larger pieces/pulling efficiency, and shaping. He did an amazing job and I can’t wait to see how he continues to progress! 

Also I have some exciting news: My classes will soon reopen to the public in August! 🍾

#art #pottery #classes #oddlysatisfying #fyp

One of my stops on my shotgun Colorado trip was learning from @dr.t_pottery  not only is he an amazing artist and talented Potter, he's a fantastic and thoughtful teacher.

As with most anything, we always want to go bigger, and push our limits. I've noticed he does a great job in throwing large amounts of clay. He's on one of the most recent episodes of The Potter's Cast w/ @pdblais Go check it out. He has an awesome story in his journey of becoming a full-time potter! 

In addition to throwing with more clay, he provided a great amount of insight for spiral wedging. Anyone else out there at a loss when it comes to that?

If you are in the Denver/Fort Collins area, you should definitely reach out to him and take a lesson! Or sign up for some studio time, or just hang out!

A Studio of Infinite Dreams! 🌌

Farewell to the old constraints and hello to a world of endless possibilities! I’m thrilled to announce the grand reopening of classes and studio time in August! 🎉

#art #pottery #oddlysatisfying #fyp

Meet my latest obsession in pottery tools! ✨ 

The ‘Do-All Trim Tool’ by Mudtools is a game-changer. Not only does it flawlessly trim pots, but it also adds a touch of magic with burnishing and intricate textures through chatter marks.

Have you had the pleasure of using this tool? Share your thoughts and experiences in the comments below!

#art #pottery #oddlysatisfying #trim #fyp

Throwing off the hump 

Can you guess what’s in the works? Here’s a hint: it’s eerily connected to Halloween.

#art #pottery #oddlysatisfying #halloween #fyp

Mastering the 3 Pound Challenge! ✨

The goal with this challenge is to achieve a 12” cylinder that your hand can still fit in with 3 pounds of clay. 

I challenge everyone to give this a try and let me how it goes in the comments! Don’t be discouraged if you can’t get 12” as it’s a very difficult feat to accomplish.

Special thanks to @mudtools for the fantastic orange sponge I’m using in this reel!

Grateful For This 2023 ❤️ 
What a wild year it’s been! I’ve transitioned from a chef to a full-time potter, showcased my art at farmers markets, and renovated a new studio space to share the joy of pottery through teaching. I’m so thankful for this amazing journey and excited for what’s next! 🚀
